<paragraph blockId="11.[136,1452,410,1409]" pageId="11" pageNumber="276">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,294,1094,1120]" pageId="11" pageNumber="276">Notes:—</emphasis>
Morphologically, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Y. P. Wu &amp; Q. R. Li" authorityYear="2021" box="[494,675,1094,1121]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Xylariaceae" genus="Astrocystis" kingdom="Fungi" order="Xylariales" pageId="11" pageNumber="276" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="multiloculata">
<emphasis box="[494,675,1094,1121]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="276">A. multiloculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from other 
<taxonomicName box="[1046,1257,1094,1121]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Xylariaceae" genus="Astrocystis" kingdom="Fungi" order="Xylariales" pageId="11" pageNumber="276" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[1046,1168,1095,1121]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="276">Astrocystis</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
by its superficial stromata, which contain many perithecia (mostly more than 8, with independent ostiole), and larger ascospores (19–25 × 7–11 μm). Phylogenetic analyses based on ITS, RPB2, β-tubulin and α-actin dataset show that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Y. P. Wu &amp; Q. R. Li" authorityYear="2021" box="[1268,1451,1166,1193]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Xylariaceae" genus="Astrocystis" kingdom="Fungi" order="Xylariales" pageId="11" pageNumber="276" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="multiloculata">
<emphasis box="[1268,1451,1166,1193]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="276">A. multiloculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
formed a well-separated clade to 
<taxonomicName box="[521,631,1203,1229]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Xylariaceae" genus="Astrocystis" kingdom="Fungi" order="Xylariales" pageId="11" pageNumber="276" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="cocoes">
<emphasis box="[521,631,1203,1229]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="276">A. cocoes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with high bootstrap support (
<figureCitation box="[974,1042,1202,1228]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[136,229,1955,1977]" captionTargetBox="[178,1409,190,1931]" captionTargetId="figure-21@2.[178,1409,190,1931]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. RAxML tree based on analysis of a combined dataset of ITS- RPB2-β-tubulin-α-actin sequence dataset from selected species of Xylariales. Bootstrap support values for maximum likelihood (ML) greater than 75%, and Bayesian posterior probabilities (BYPP) greater than 0.90 are given at the nodes. Strain numbers are noted after the species names. The tree is rooted to the outgroup of Daldinia loculatoides (CBS 113279), D. macaronesica (CBS 113040) and Hypoxylon rickii (MUCL 53309)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5565848" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5565848/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="276">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Y. P. Wu &amp; Q. R. Li" authorityYear="2021" box="[1069,1350,1202,1229]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Xylariaceae" genus="Astrocystis" kingdom="Fungi" order="Xylariales" pageId="11" pageNumber="276" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="multiloculata">
<emphasis box="[1069,1350,1202,1229]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="276">Astrocystis multiloculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
shows a close relationship with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Viegas" authorityYear="1944" box="[404,596,1238,1264]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Xylariaceae" genus="Kretzschmariella" kingdom="Fungi" order="Xylariales" pageId="11" pageNumber="276" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[404,596,1238,1264]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="276">Kretzschmariella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in terms of stromata. Both have stromata containing many perithecia, and ascospores with straight germ slit slightly less than spore-length, but 
<taxonomicName authority="(Cooke) Y. M. Ju &amp; J. D. Rogers" authorityName="Y. M. Ju &amp; J. D. Rogers" baseAuthorityName="Cooke" box="[931,1451,1274,1301]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Xylariaceae" genus="Kretzschmariella" kingdom="Fungi" order="Xylariales" pageId="11" pageNumber="276" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="culmorum">
<emphasis box="[931,1080,1274,1300]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="276">K. culmorum</emphasis>
(Cooke) Y.M. Ju &amp; J.D. Rogers
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Ju, Y. M. &amp; Rogers, J. D." box="[144,350,1310,1337]" pageId="11" pageNumber="276" pagination="242" refId="ref11352" refString="Ju, Y. M. &amp; Rogers, J. D. (1994) Kretzschmariella culmorum. Mycotaxon 51: 242." type="journal article" year="1994">Ju &amp; Rogers 1994</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<taxonomicName authority="Viegas" authorityName="Viegas" box="[413,626,1310,1336]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Xylariaceae" genus="Kretzschmariella" kingdom="Fungi" order="Xylariales" pageId="11" pageNumber="276" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="guaduae">
<emphasis box="[413,542,1310,1336]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="276">K. guaduae</emphasis>
Viégas
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Viegas, K. G." box="[641,783,1310,1336]" pageId="11" pageNumber="276" pagination="105" refId="ref12941" refString="Viegas, K. G. (1994) Kretzschmariella guaduae. Bragantia 4: 105." type="journal article" year="1994">Viégas 1994</bibRefCitation>
) usually bear a cellular appendage on immature ascospores which distinguish them from 
<emphasis box="[475,666,1346,1373]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="276">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Y. P. Wu &amp; Q. R. Li" authorityYear="2021" box="[475,662,1346,1373]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Xylariaceae" genus="Astrocystis" kingdom="Fungi" order="Xylariales" pageId="11" pageNumber="276" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="multiloculata">A. multiloculata</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
Moreover, the phylogenetic tree shows that it is more reasonable to place 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Y. P. Wu &amp; Q. R. Li" authorityYear="2021" box="[202,382,1382,1409]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Xylariaceae" genus="Astrocystis" kingdom="Fungi" order="Xylariales" pageId="11" pageNumber="276" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="multiloculata">
<emphasis box="[202,382,1382,1409]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="276">A. multiloculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<emphasis box="[418,548,1383,1409]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="276">
<taxonomicName box="[418,543,1383,1409]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Xylariaceae" genus="Astrocystis" kingdom="Fungi" order="Xylariales" pageId="11" pageNumber="276" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">Astrocystis</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
